370 g Striploin Steak
400 g Yellow Potato
1 unit(s) Ciabatta Roll
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
7 g Parsley
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
56 g Spring Mix
113 g Baby Tomatoes
28 g Almonds, sliced
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
¼ tsp Salt*
¼ tsp Pepper*

Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add potatoes, half the Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to the prepared baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, stirring halfway, until tender and golden, 18-22 min.

Meanwhile, halve tomaotes.
Roughly chop parsley.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Halve, then cut ciabatta into 1/2 inch pieces.
Add tomatoes, vinegar, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp sugar) to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper and stir to coat.
Add pesto, garlic and half the parsley to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to mix. This is your romesco sauce.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add half the garlic spread. Swirl the pan until melted, 30 sec.
Add ciabatta. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until starting to turn golden, 2-3 min.
Add almonds. Cook, stirring often, until croutons are crispy and almonds are toasted, 2-3 min.
Transfer to a plate. Carefully wipe out pan.

Pat steak dry with paper towels. Season with salt, pepper and remaining Smoked-Paprika Garlic Blend.
Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then steak. Sear until golden, 1-2 per side.
Remove from heat and transfer steak to an unlined baking sheet. Roast in the bottom of the oven until cooked to desired doneness, 6-9 min.**

When steak is done, transfer to a cutting board. Loosely cover with foil and set aside to rest, 5 min.
When potatoes are done, remove from oven. Add remaining garlic spread and remaining parsley to potatoes directly on baking sheet. Stir to mix.

Add spring mix and crouton-almond mixture to the bowl with tomatoes. Toss to coat.
Thinly slice steak.
Divide potatoes and salad between plates.
Top potatoes with steak.
Spoon romesco sauce over steak.
Sprinkle feta over salad.

If you've opted for striploin steak, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the sirloin steak.